elements.name: districtPortOfEntrySummary
elements.description: A code representing the district/port of entry summary. Valid district/port codes can be queried through the Extract Reference File chapter of this publication.

elements.name: entryFilerCode
elements.description: A unique code assigned by CBP to all active entry document preparers. The Entry Filer Code occupies the first three positions of an entry number regardless of where the entry is filed.

elements.name: filler1
elements.description: Space fill. Reserved filler for possible future expansion of Entry Filer Code and/or Entry Number.

elements.name: entryNumber
elements.description: The number assigned to the entry. For additional information on valid entry formats.

elements.name: antidumpingDutyAmount
elements.description: A value representing the total antidumping duty amount. Two decimal places are implied. If the duty is a whole number, the two low-order (cents) positions contain zeroes.

elements.name: countervailingDutyAmount
elements.description: A value representing the total countervailing duty. Two decimal places are implied. If the duty is a whole number, the two low-order (cents) positions contain zeroes.

elements.name: payIndicator
elements.description: A code of Y (yes) indicates payment is due; N (no) indicates there is no payment due. If the code is N, the transaction amount is not included in the total on Record Identifier Q4.

elements.name: countervailingIndicator
elements.description: A code of Y (yes) indicates payment is due; N (no) indicates payment is covered under bond. If the code is N, the associated transaction amount is not included in the total on Record Identifier Q4.

elements.name: antidumpingIndicator
elements.description: A code of Y (yes) indicates payment is due; N (no) indicates payment is covered under bond. If the code is N, the associated transaction amount is not included in the total on Record Identifier Q4.

elements.name: teamNumber
elements.description: A code indicating the CBP Import Specialist Team assigned to the entry summary.

elements.name: interestAmountForReconciliationSummary
elements.description: A value representing the interest amount for reconciliation summary. Two decimal places are implied. If the interest is a whole number, the two low-order (cents) positions contain zeroes.
